The moon decided one night that it was tired of just watching the ocean sparkle, so it leaned a little closer—just enough to whisper secrets into the tides. The waves, delighted by the attention, began dancing more wildly than usual, crashing and curling like they were trying to impress an old friend. Somewhere on the shore, a stray cat paused mid-step, sensing that something subtle but important had shifted in the world. And for a brief moment, everything—sky, sea, and silence—felt like it was in on the same quiet joke.
